description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Learning and Development Manager&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have a background in learning &amp; development and are looking for your next role? You may be an L&amp;D Advisor, Trainer or in an HR role with experience of training/OD and be comfortable working in a progressive and results orientated environment. An NHS background is desirable, however, it is equally important that the post holder can adopt a business focused approach to managing our L&amp;D operation and help equip our workforce to provide high standards of patient care. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking someone to join our friendly supportive department and provide a combination of training delivery, design and management support within a small team based at East Surrey Hospital. The role offers a unique opportunity for someone wishing to further develop their professional practice and play a key role in our ambitious learning and development agenda.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Reporting to the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Associate Director of Learning and Organisational Development &lt;span&gt;you will also be responsible for managing training administration and ensuring that the team provide a customer focused and professional service. The Learning &amp; Development Manager has a diverse range of responsibilities including the Trust’s induction and mandatory training programme and coordinating a suite of personal effectiveness workshops. A key area of work in the coming year will be further development of processes and training to support the Trust talent management strategy. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal chat about the role, please contact &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Associate Director of Learning and Organisational Development &lt;span&gt;via email adele.kendrick@nhs.net or by phone 01737 768511 X6192.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role (37.5 hours), Monday to Friday.  Candidates will need to have flexibility to cover service needs between the core hours of 9am to 5pm with occasional earlier starts from 8/8.30am.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adele Kendrick Associate Director of Learning and Organisational Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;adele.kendrick@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: Sunday 22 November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Monday 30 November&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
